items.text:
**CASTINGCALL!!! (Ulønnet)**

Hejsa. vi er i gang med vores andet projekt her på Potemkin, den jyske filmskole - Masterclass. Vi søger derfor skuespillere til Hovedrollen **Alfred**.

Logline: “**Spildt Mælk**” I denne absurde coming-of-age komedie, om identitet, vaner og det at finde sig selv,  møder vi Alfred en ung mand der flytter til storbyen for at starte sit voksenliv. Alt imens hans bizarre afhængighed af mælk vender op og ned på hans nye hverdag og skaber kaos.

**Alfred** (21-25) er en usikker ung gut der lige er flyttet fra landet og ind til storbyen. 

Denne transition er temmelig hård for en så tilbageholdende og usikker dreng som ham, og for at gøre det endnu værre så har han en afhængighed til mælk. Hvordan forklarer man lige sine nye roomies om det? Alfred er godhjertet og ser altid det bedste i folk og vil gerne lære folk at kende, men fordi han er rimelig kejtet så formår han nærmest altid at få et allerede nyt akavet møde til at blive endnu mere akavet.

Optagelserne foregår i Aarhus C den **21. og 22. oktober**. 

der vil være forplejning på set, men jobbet er ulønnet.

vedhæftet dette opslag er scene 01-03 som vi gerne vil se dit bud på i et selftape sendt til min mail. (showreel er velkommen, men vi foretrækker selftape til de valgte scener)

Mvh. Team **Spildt Mælk**. - Potemkin

Bastiankapela@gmail.com

items.text:
Du möchtest als Schauspielerin im Training bleiben, aber Dir fehlt eine gute Gruppe? Dann komme zum FLINTA*s Acting Lab!
Es erwartet Dich ein Mix aus Übungen und Improszenen, damit Du lernst Deinen Impulsen zu vertrauen und an Deiner Durchlässigkeit und Wahrhaftigkeit zu arbeiten. Ich schaffe einen sicheren und geschützen Raum, in dem Du Dich ausprobieren kannst. Mir ist es wichtig, die FLINTA* Community zu stärken und freue mich, wenn diese immer weiter wächst. 
Das Training geht 3 Stunden und kostet Dich 20€. 
Wenn Du dabei sein möchtest, dann schreib mir gern eine Mail mit Deinem Material und kurz etwas zu Deiner Person an: contact@sophieriva.com. 
Ich nehme Dich gern auf die Warteliste und informiere Dich mit allen Infos sobald es im Herbst losgeht! 
Ich freue mich auf Dich!

Deine Sophie

items.text:
**Hello to all the actors, aspiring actors, and curious creatives out there— this one’s for you!**

 

I’m a Berlin-based director and teacher launching a small actor training space called **Studio LeBolt**, and I’m offering **a 2-day** **monologue workshop in English** this September.

 

It’s a supportive space for anyone — beginner or experienced — looking to reconnect with acting, build confidence, and develop a strong audition-ready piece. Whether you’re returning to performance, building your showreel, or just want to explore something new— you’re welcome.

 

My work is rooted in embodiment, presence, and, most of all, play. I’d love for you to join us!

 

**info + registration:**

dates: September 6 & 13 (13:00–17:00)

**Early bird sign up only until Aug. 14**

location: Treptower Park (Park Studio)

register: stephanielebolt.com/studio-lebolt

 

 

Happy to answer any questions or send more details — and would be grateful if you passed it on to someone who might be looking for something like this.

Stephanie xo

items.text:
🎬 Casting Call – Student Short Film (UNPAID)

Production Title: Baggage

Role: Protagonist – Old Man

Requirement: Male actor in his 50s or 60s, preferably with a beard. Tall and skinny physique.

Shooting Dates: 18th – 19th September

Location: Berlin

As this is a passion-driven student short film, the role is unpaid, but catering will be provided throughout the shoot days.

Synopsis:

In a world where emotional burdens are physical baggage, an old man struggles to carry his load through a park. He longs to climb a sunlit hill but is held back by his heavy suitcases. He repeatedly rejects the help of a mysterious, baggage-free blonde man who offers him a pair of scissors to cut the rope binding him to his past. After a failed attempt to build a shelter from his bags and a collapse that leaves him injured, the old man finally accepts the scissors. Realizing he has the power to choose his path, he cuts the rope, freeing himself from his burden. The blonde man vanishes, and the old man, now unencumbered, finally climbs the hill, symbolizing his newfound freedom.

📧 If interested, please reach out to:

Kole Jackson (Director)– kole.jackson.m@gmail.com

Ahad Khan (Assistant Director)– ahadg8@gmail.com

We are looking for a party-hostess (female) to korean karaoke bar!🎉
District 7, two minutes from Blaha Luiza
What we offer:
✔️6 000HUF/hour + 100% of the tips
✔️Flexible working hours
✔️Weakly payment 
✔️It’s can be full or part of job, depends on your schedule 
✔️ party vibe, amazing team and guests 
Your tasks:
➖taking orders
➖Pouring drinks
➖Entertaining guests (just basic conversation), singing with them, creating fun and good atmosphere
If  u are: till 30 y.o, attractive, positive, cheerful and energetic, u have basic communication skills in English then we are waiting for u!🫶
For more details, please,send dm!

Aktorka / statystka do krótkiego filmu – kampanii społecznej 

Szukamy kobiety z Łodzi lub okolic, dyspozycyjnej w środę, 8 października 2025 r.

👉 Rola: pracowniczka magazynu / sklepu (scena symboliczna).
📍 Miejsce: studio filmowe w Łodzi, ul. Krzemieniecka  (okolice Atlas Areny).
🕚 Start nagrań: godz. 11:00.
🎥 Po nagraniu w studiu planowane są krótkie przebitki w magazynie (również w Łodzi).

🌐 Pole eksploatacji filmu: internet.

Zgłoszenia wraz z krótką wizytówką video prosimy przesyłać na adres:
📩 praca@goodeye.com.pl

Szukamy wyłącznie osób dyspozycyjnych w tym terminie!!!

items.text:
Casting call · 04.10 · 14:00–16:00 · Kraków

When and where: October 4, 14:00–16:00, Kraków, Romanowicza 19b. 

The project: student independent short film, prepared for submission to European festivals and media exposure.
Plot: action takes place 30 years from our time; a dystopia about the "oppression" of the body and rebellion against a repressive regime.
Who do you work with: a professional team led by director
What the artists will get: promotion in our social networks, the opportunity to use filmed materials in the portfolio, visibility at European festivals.
The film is independent - payment for shifts is not provided, agreement on commissions in case of success of the film and awards.
Organizer: Theatre studio "Bez Uprzedzeń" (NIP 6793287079).
Filming: 2–3 shifts in the window of October 15–31, 2025 (exact dates to be confirmed).

We are careful about the topic of the film and the boundaries of the artists: any sensitive actions (for example, a kiss) - only with your express consent, under safe conditions. No nudity without separate agreement. There is zero tolerance for harassment and discrimination on the site. 

Who are we looking for?
The main roles:
- Female, 20–30 years old. Height 160–175, clothing size S–M. Natural European appearance, feminine. Blonde/brown/light shoulder-length hair or longer, straight or wavy. The eyes are light or light brown. Fluent  English required
- Male, 20–30 years old. Height 178–195, athletic physique (natural dramatik appearance). Short dark blond or dark hair, straight or with a slight wave. No beard or with light facial hair. Fluent  English required
- Male, 25–40 years old. Slender, possible androgynous type. An expressive gaze and mimics, large eyes, dark haired. Preferably clean shaven. Visible tattoos/piercings are allowed (moderately).

Episodes / Cameos:
- Woman, 20–35 years old. Height 165–180, "dramatic" type: expressive green or dark brown eyes, full lips, dark/black hair.
- Dancers (4 performers): Women with good plasticity; the ability to improvise to club music solo and in interaction.
Group of club visitors (5 performers):
- 3 men 30–50 — strong physique, pronounced natural hair is allowed.
- 2 women 20–30 — short, slender, elegant constitution.
- male couple (2 performers), comfortable with interaction on the camera, including a screen kiss (with your consent).
A couple with a performative BDSM image (2 performers):
- The dominant figure - tall, large; any age/gender; comfortable wearing heels/platform shoes.
- Submissive partner - possible representation in latex and a mask (including a stylized one). Only with full consent, without dangerous practices; closed playground; interactions are agreed in advance.
- A girl with pronounced aesthetic modifications. For example: enlarged breasts, thick false eyelashes, voluminous lips.
- Passers-by on the street, M/F, different types and ages

For participating in casting please fill in the form:

items.text:
CASTING CALL

Production Company: GreenHouse Films Production

Project Type: BFA Short Film

Union Status: Non-Union

Pay Status: Unpaid Projected

Shooting Dates: TBD

Shooting Location: Orlando area

Summary: A lonely girl shunned by her school finds comfort in plants and in the one friend who truly sees her.

We have not set an exact shoot date, but we plan to begin filming sometime in November. This is an unpaid project - copy and credit will be given to all involved. This is a non-union production.

Character Breakdowns:

MONOMAY: Female, Late Teens (20s), A teen girl marked by facial scars and iris coloboma, finds purpose and comfort in tending to her beloved plants.

JASON: Male, Late Teens (20s), The school's "Golden Boy" athlete, hides his insecurities behind charisma.

FAN CLUB: Any gender, Teens (20s), A group of students that fawn over Jason and seek his attention.

How to Submit: Please send an email to greenhousefilmsproduction@gmail.com to reserve a time slot for auditions.

**Casting Call — vertical advertisement and reels (Vancouver Laser & Skin Care Centre)**

Hello everyone!

We are casting talent for vertical ads and reels to promote our clinic’s largest annual event.

**Roles Needed**

1 male + 2 female talents

Age range: 25–35

Ethnicity: Caucasian or East Asian

English: native fluency required

Preferred (not required): experience in social media content, beauty industry, or ad shoots

**Project Details**

Deliverables: 3 vertical videos (ads/fun reels)

Shoot Duration: 3–3.5 hours (approx., minor fluctuations possible)

Dates: Shooting between October 8–10 (exact date TBD)
Location: 750 W Broadway, Vancouver, BC V5Z 1K1

**Compensation**

$300 flat rate

1 selected treatment (BBL or PicoWay, value $500)

**How to Apply**

Please send the following to **marketing@vancouverlaser.com**

with the subject line:

**Project Beauty + [Your Name]**

Headshot

Resume

Demo videos (if available)

If you have any questions, feel free to reach out. Thank you all!

items.text:
My name is Adelola Mary Haastrup, and I’m a passionate actress currently based in Nigeria. I’m looking to expand my career in the UK and am actively seeking opportunities for visa sponsorship.

I started acting at the age of 7, performing in stage productions. While much of my early work was in gospel theater, I’m not particularly religious, and my focus has always been on the craft of acting. I’m eager to explore a wide range of roles in film, TV, theater, and commercial work, and I’m excited to branch out into new genres and experiences.

In addition to my acting experience, I studied Music Technology with a major in Stage Performing Arts for 2 years , and I have full documentation of all my final projects from that time. This technical training complements my stage performance and has given me a comprehensive understanding of both the artistic and technical sides of the industry.

I was also part of a gospel drama group form 2011 to 2020 , where I won 4 "Card Awards," including Best Actress  (twice), Best Dressed, and Best Minister. These awards reflect my dedication to the craft, and I’m incredibly proud of them.

I’m looking forward to collaborating on a wide range of acting roles in the UK’s vibrant and inclusive creative industry, and I’m actively seeking potential employers who are willing to support visa sponsorships for skilled performers like me.

If you have any leads or know of any production companies, agents, or casting opportunities, I would love to hear from you! Please feel free to DM me or comment below.

Thank you so much for your time and consideration. I look forward to connecting with you all!

AMERIVENTS is Hiring!

We’re excited to assemble our Dream Team of talented professionals for iconic NYC events like SNL wrap parties, movie premieres, and sporting events.

**Building Our Dream Team**

At Amerivents, we are committed to assembling and empowering a "Dream Team" of talented individuals who bring diverse skills, shared values, and a unified purpose to every endeavor. Much like a championship sports team, we believe that our collective success is built on the strength and collaboration of our team members, each contributing their unique expertise to achieve exceptional results.

**Now Hiring FRONT OF HOUSE:**
* Catering Hospitality Staff
* Servers
* Bartenders
* Captains

**Now Hiring BACK OF HOUSE:**
* Dishwasher
* Utility
* Grill Cook
* Line Cook

**Requirements:**

2+ years of catering or high-end retail experience

You must be 18 or older

**Next Steps:**
1. Complete the interview survey here: [https://forms.gle/r3B2ib3kssxRfF5v8](https://forms.gle/r3B2ib3kssxRfF5v8)
2. Visit[ www.amerivents.com](http://www.amerivents.com/) and click “Apply” (mention “CORE-NYC” in the referral box).

**Why Amerivents?**
* Fast-paced, exciting, and team-oriented work environment
* Flexible schedules—you choose your availability!
* Gain unforgettable experiences in the hospitality industry
* Experience unique and inspiring event locations!

**What We’re Looking For:**
* 2+ years of catering or high-end retail experience
* Professional, adaptable, and radiate positivity team players
* Composure under pressure and ability to adapt to dynamic environments
* Flexible and reliable team players who can seamlessly adjust to varying roles and tasks
* Ability to lift 50 lbs and stand for extended periods

**To Our Team:**
We offer the chance to pursue your passions while contributing to a company that values your unique talents and provides the support you need to excel.

We look forward to hearing from you!

**This is not an official job offer**

items.text:
CASTING CALL - PRESENTER FOR SOCIAL MEDIA CAMPAIGN FOR FINANCIAL SERVICES COMPANY IN LONDON (POTENTIALLY 13th OCTOBER)

Hi all, we’re currently casting for a presenter for a short social media video with us. We’re looking for someone with experience presenting, who can share links for us to review.

We’re hoping for someone with bags of personality who’s happy and confident to approach people in the street and stoke up a conversation, but you’ll also be required to deliver a piece to camera. You’d need to be very confident riding a bike and have a decent level of fitness, as we’ll be following you cycle around London for a couple of hours on a branded bike.

Please only send on details if you have Presenting experience, with links to recent work. Email details to casting@feral-films.com. Please do not DM me, only send details via email.

This is a paid role, with travel (to and from the location within London) and sustenance all covered on the shoot.

The shoot date is pencilled for the 13th October, this may change however. The location is likely to be Central London. 

Thank you!

items.text:
Film crews are using Photoshop IDs and hand over cash envelopes to get paid?

Saturation's co-founders Jens Jacob & Simon Tam break down why film production financial tools haven't evolved like Figma, Frame.io, and Airtable did for their industries and how they're building the solution. From 20+ years in tech at Microsoft, Yahoo & Splunk to revolutionizing how $2B+ in budgets get managed for productions. Trusted by over 8,000 producers.

items.groupTitle: LA Actors, Agents, Casting Directors, Producers
items.summary:
Film crews are using Photoshop IDs and hand over cash envelopes to get paid?

Saturation's co-founders Jens Jacob & Simon Tam break down why film production financial tools haven't evolved like Figma, Frame.io, and Airtable did for their industries and how they're building the solution. From 20+ years in tech at Microsoft, Yahoo & Splunk to revolutionizing how $2B+ in budgets get managed for productions. Trusted by over 8,000 producers.

Booking for the next intake for Meisner 1, 
IS NOW OPEN! ✨

Come join our community! 🫶

Train for Authenticity, Perform with Power. 🎭🎬

Book now!

Unleash your authentic self and discover new emotional depths in your performances. The Meisner technique transforms more than just your acting—it transforms you.

Class is limited to 10 students. 

Meisner Technique - Intro & Repetition Skills
Book Now @ https://www.lawrencecarmichael.com/meisner-intro
 Consent-informed connection and sustainable emotional exploration - unlock your true potential!

📅 Course Details:
* Dates: Wednesdays, 4 pm – 7 pm
* Duration: 29th October - 3rd December 
* Location: Marylebone, London
* Class Size: Limited to 10 places for personal attention

🎟️ What’s Included: ✅ Six guided in-person sessions ✅ 1 personalised feedback session ✅ 1 FREE drop-in Actor Training Session for continued practice 🎉

Whether you’re a beginner or an experienced actor looking to refresh your skills, this course will help you tap into deeper dynamics and develop truthful behaviour in your work.

💰 Fees:
* £220 for 20+ hours of training
* £200 each if you bring a friend (save £20 each!) 💥

The Meisner Technique has consistently proven to build truthful, dynamic acting—the glue that ties all disciplines together! 💡 Join us in a fun, supportive environment that fosters genuine connection and growth. 🌱

BOOK NOW: @ Meisner 1 - Intro | lawrencecarmichael
Or email - mail@lawrencecarmichael.com

⚡ Limited to just 10 places—secure your spot today! ⚡

items.text:
We're casting for our magical Christmas Grotto experience in the Milton Keynes and Bedford area and we’re on the lookout for a charismatic, professional Mother Christmas to join the team!

📍 Location: 2 venues across MILTON KEYNES & BEDFORD
MK44 3QP & MK17 8UE
📆 Contract: December 2025
💸 Rate: £20 per hour

✨ Requirements:

• Entry-level acting skills

• Basic script work and immersive performance ability

• Confident group singing of children’s Christmas songs

• Must absolutely love Christmas!

You’ll be part of a heartwarming festive experience for families and children, in a beautifully themed setting. 

🧝‍♀️ We’re looking for:

• Confident, energetic performers with great improvisation skills

• Friendly, reliable team players

• Previous experience working with children or in character-based roles is a plus

📌 Important Info:

• Costume and full training provided

• Paid rehearsals and site visits will be scheduled in early November – exact dates TBC

• Below is the confirmed list of working dates and shift times:

Tue, Dec 2 – 1:30 PM to 7:00 PM

Thu, Dec 4 – 1:30 PM to 6:00 PM

Tue, Dec 9 – 10:30 AM to 5:00 PM

Tue, Dec 16 – 10:30 AM to 7:00 PM

Fri, Dec 19 – 8:30 AM to 6:00 PM

Sat, Dec 20 – 8:30 AM to 6:00 PM

📩 To apply:
Send your CV, headshot, and any relevant performance footage to: castings@evokeents.com
Subject line: MOTHER CHRISTMAS CONTRACT
Tell us a little about why you’d be a great fit & the dates you're interested in working — we’d love to hear from you!

😲Amazingly flexible! Stunningly beautiful!🌸💫🌸

Such incredible skills! Honestly, it left me speechless.👏🏻🌷💝

🎟️ Visit https://1kb.link/gzbqY3 for information about a theater near you.

⚡️ Don’t miss your chance to witness the magic and grace of a live performance that will leave you breathless. 💫

🙋‍♀️ In Firebird Turn, the dancer would initiate the turn by kicking her leg back so high that it almost touches the crowd of her head. She would then maintain that hold while completing her turns. Under this graceful move lies a combination of strength, flexibility and coordination that takes countless hours to perfect.

📲 Tag a friend who needs to see this with you! 💖

#ShenYun #ShenYun2026 #Ballet #Dance

Na plan filmu, którego akcja dzieje się w latach współczesnych, poszukujemy statystów:

▪️ kobiet i mężczyzn każdej narodowości w wieku 18-30 lat jako studentów

▪️ kobiet i mężczyzn w wieku ok 40-60 lat jako wykładowców 

▪️ mężczyznę w wieku ok 50 lat z psem (1 scena) 

Studenci i wykładowcy- część scen w plenerze, a część w budynku. Stawka w zależności od godzin na planie 110-130 gotówką po planie. 

Zgłoszenia wraz z imieniem i nazwiskiem, numerem telefonu, AKTUALNYMI zdjęciami (sylwetka, twarz), przyjmujemy na adres: CASTING@ONSETAGENCY.PL w tytule wpisując „NIEDZIELA”.

items.text:
Ich bin vielleicht nicht der geborene Top-Schauspieler oder das nächste Supermodel für die Kamera – in der Werbekommunikation überlasse ich das Rampenlicht gerne anderen. ABER ich habe etwas Großes im Sinn und bin bereit, einen neuen Weg zu gehen: Ich möchte das Medienhaus Mond Jung eröffnen! 🌙🌟

​Dieses Medienhaus ist keine spontane Idee; ich habe es über längere Zeit entwickelt, und es verfügt bereits über einige hauseigene Marken. Doch jetzt bin ich an einem spannenden und entscheidenden Punkt angekommen.  

Die Zeit der reinen Werbemittel-Produktion ist vorbei. Um die Vision von Mond Jung vollständig zu verwirklichen, muss ich Maschinen anschaffen, um haptische Ware (also physische Produkte!) produzieren zu können. 📦⚙️ 

​Um diesen nächsten Schritt zu machen und Mond Jung richtig voranzubringen, suche ich Unterstützung!

​Besonders an euch aus der Schauspiel- und Kreativszene gerichtet: Ich suche dringend Leute, die sich mit dem Medienhaus Mond Jung identifizieren und es als Vertreter (oder Promotor) auf die nächste Ebene heben möchten.  

Eure Präsenz und euer Netzwerk sind Gold wert, um unsere Marken bekannt zu machen! 🤝

​Wer hat Lust, Teil dieser spannenden Reise zu sein und Mond Jung mit aufzubauen? Schreibt mir eine DM, lasst uns connecten und dieses Ding zum Fliegen bringen! 💌

​#MondJung #Medienhaus #NeuesProjekt #Startup #Kreativszene #SchauspielerGesucht #Unterstützung #Vision

items.text:
**CASTINGCALL!!! (Ulønnet)**

Hejsa. vi er i gang med vores andet projekt her på Potemkin, den jyske filmskole - Masterclass. Vi søger derfor skuespillere til Hovedrollen **Alfred**.

Logline: “**Spildt Mælk**” I denne absurde coming-of-age komedie, om identitet, vaner og det at finde sig selv,  møder vi Alfred en ung mand der flytter til storbyen for at starte sit voksenliv. Alt imens hans bizarre afhængighed af mælk vender op og ned på hans nye hverdag og skaber kaos.

**Alfred** (21-25) er en usikker ung gut der lige er flyttet fra landet og ind til storbyen. 

Denne transition er temmelig hård for en så tilbageholdende og usikker dreng som ham, og for at gøre det endnu værre så har han en afhængighed til mælk. Hvordan forklarer man lige sine nye roomies om det? Alfred er godhjertet og ser altid det bedste i folk og vil gerne lære folk at kende, men fordi han er rimelig kejtet så formår han nærmest altid at få et allerede nyt akavet møde til at blive endnu mere akavet.

Optagelserne foregår i Aarhus C den **21. og 22. oktober**. 

der vil være forplejning på set, men jobbet er ulønnet.

vedhæftet dette opslag er scene 01-03 som vi gerne vil se dit bud på i et selftape sendt til min mail. (showreel er velkommen, men vi foretrækker selftape til de valgte scener)

Mvh. Team **Spildt Mælk**. - Potemkin

Bastiankapela@gmail.com

Dzień Dobry, do projektu edukacyjnego poszukujemy dzieci w wieku 3-8 lat razem z opiekunami: rodzicami, z mamą lub tatą, lub mama i tatą, bądź dziadkiem i babcią. Zainteresowane osoby prosimy o kontakt firma@studiohoryzont.com.pl

Gatunek muzyki: elektropop
Budżet: jest (do ustalenia)

Scenariusz: dziwny, mroczny i ze specyficznym poczuciem humoru
Lokacja: Warszawa/Żyrardów, industrialna pracownia lamp artystycznych. Dowieziemy i odwieziemy
Czas pracy: 12 h w nocy, ok.18:00 - 6:00 
Ekipa: kameralna i przyjaźnie nastawiona 

Kogo szukamy? 
Kogoś o nieoczywistej urodzie, niekoniecznie w kanonie piękna,
kto nie boi się kamery i lubi trochę poeksperymentować.

Termin nagrań: październik (do ustalenia)

Zgłoszenia: w komentarzu lub w wiadomości prywatnej. Z góry dzięki - odezwiemy się do wybranych.

sharedPost.text:
A HUGE thank you to everyone who has taken the time to apply, we’ve smashed the number of applicants we’ve had previously which is amazing! 😱
We’ve highlighted the key points to note:

📌 We’re a small agency and are incredibly busy at the moment, we appreciate people want to know but we cannot give updates throughout the screening process and replying to emails asking for information stops us being able to process applications

📌 If you have applied during the book opening period you will be notified whether successful or not but please bear with us as we work through applications

📌 Our social team have NO access to any information
regarding applications

📌 Our in person assessment day will be Sunday 19th October for successful applicants

📌 We will post on socials once we have contacted all applicants

📌 Also to clarify, you don’t get a confirmation email when you completed the application, if you were able to submit, it will have gone through. 🙂

And again thank you to everyone who took the time to apply we’ve got our fingers crossed for you all!
#thedramamob

CASTING CALL – FEMALE LEAD (Short Film “Failsafe”)

LOCATION: Banbury, Oxfordshire, UK

PRODUCTION DATES: One weekend – either 11–12, 18–19, or 25–26 October 2025

PAID, UNPAID OR PROFIT SHARE: Paid – £250 for 2 days + travel considered

ABOUT THE PROJECT:

Failsafe is a psychological short film currently in production with a professional crew. Directed by award-winning filmmaker, whose previous film Time Spent earned 23 awards, 22 nominations, and an 8.8 IMDb rating.

The final scenes are being cast for this dynamic and visually intense project, which will be submitted to national and international festivals and featured in Pro Movie Maker Magazine.

FEMALE LEAD

• Age Range: 25–35

• Character Description:�A game designer whose perception of reality begins to fracture and blur with the digital world she created. This role demands psychological nuance, emotional range, and depth — from confidence and strength to vulnerability and doubt.

• 2-day shoot (Saturday + Sunday)

• Choose one of these weekends:

◦ 11–12 October 2025

◦ 18–19 October 2025

◦ 25–26 October 2025

• Professional set and crew

• Self-tape audition required

• Reasonable travel costs considered

items.text:
📣🎬 Casting Call – Short Mockumentary Film 

We are casting for ‘A Race with Ian Hitchworth’, a 3-minute mockumentary short film made as part of our final year at UWE Bristol. The film will be shot in Bristol in the week commencing 3rd November 2025 (exact dates TBC). This is a student project, unpaid, but with expenses covered. The film is intended for university showcase and festival submission.

Story:�Ian Hitchworth, son of a respected track runner, was once a rising sprint star. Years later, he resurfaces in a humiliating viral TikTok, and a small documentary crew captures his desperate bid to matter again—culminating in a shambolic charity race. Told in a deadpan, mockumentary style, the film mixes awkward comedy with moments of vulnerability as Ian’s arrogance clashes with his insecurities.

Roles:
Ian Hitchworth (Lead)�25, male. Wannabe track star with inflated self-belief and fragile confidence. To the camera, he’s arrogant, overconfident, and insists on being taken seriously — but cracks show through awkward silences and moments of panic. Actor must have strong comedic timing, improvisational instincts, and be comfortable with physical comedy (running, awkward costume, frustrated energy). Needs to balance deadpan humour with flashes of real vulnerability.

Interviewer (Supporting)�Any age/gender. Calm, inquisitive presence behind the camera, provoking Ian with offhand questions and blunt corrections. Think Nick Broomfield style: slightly awkward, matter-of-fact, not intentionally funny but often humorous through honesty. Delivery should be dry and understated. Voice-only, but may appear briefly on camera.

Race Official / Athletes (Supporting & Extras)�18–40, any gender. Includes a race official who ushers Ian onto the track (Small Speaking Role), plus authentic-looking athletes for the race sequence. Non-speaking, but must look natural on a track.

Apply by: 27th Ocotber 2025�To Apply: Please send a headshot, CV (or Spotlight/Mandy link), and any showreel/self-tape to Scarlet2.Gerry@live.uwe.ac.uk

items.text:
CASTING CALL – Independent Short Film (LONDON)

We are casting for an upcoming student short film exploring obsession, ambition, and the dark side of the ballet world.

Production: Student film via The American University of Rome

Director: Maxine Sutton

Cinematographer: Georgia Blackson

Shooting Dates: December 12–19

ROLES

NATASHA (Lead)

Female, 18–28

Ballet-trained (advanced preferred)

Must convey vulnerability, intensity, and psychological depth

Strong acting, presence, and physical performance required

Slavic accent preferred.

Pay: 250€ flat rate for entire production

RUDOLPH

Male, 25–40

Dance experience preferred

Embodies both beauty and cruelty — a man who inspires awe, fear, and complete submission.

Slavic accent preferred.

Pay: 250€ flat rate for entire production

SYNOPSIS

Natasha, a talented but tormented ballerina, navigates a high-stakes audition that tests the limits of her physical and psychological endurance. As she strives for perfection under the watchful eye of the enigmatic Rudolph, the line between reality and terror begins to blur, forcing her to confront the true cost of ambition.

TO APPLY

Please complete the audition form and send it, along with a headshot, to: maxineclairesutton@gmail.com

sharedPost.text:
I’ve been a model and actor for over 30 years, and as a certified mindset coach, I’ve also had the privilege of helping my daughter strengthen her mindset and grow her career with co-star, supporting, and supporting lead roles in projects for Paramount +, CBS, Hallmark, and more. Most recently, she appears as Rachel in Amazon Prime’s Top 10* *show* The Runarounds*.

﻿

I've been asked a lot over the years to share my experience and help other parents and young actors along on their acting journeys; that’s why I’m hosting a **free webinar on October 19** where you'll learn:
* Mindset strategies I taught my daughter (and use with my actor clients)
* The realities of building a career in acting—what most people *don’t*tell you
* The pros and cons of pursuing an acting degree
* Strategies we've used to open up audition and booking opportunties
* PLUS: get the inside scoop as my daughter shares her experience on *The Runarounds*: from first audition to being on set.

🎟️ Don't wait! Get all the details and save your spot here → [[Register Now]](https://campaign-statistics.com/link_click/e9VEqJ-gpxZ2D6-4ysUg9/a85533005915d0327bef8a6796583a43)

﻿

📅 **Date: October 19, 2025 **

🕔 **Time:** **4:00pm-5:30pm EST**

﻿

While this webinar is geared towards young actors & their parents, **actors of all levels **will benefit from this session. We will have an open, honest conversation that gives you clarity, direction, and encouragement as you navigate the acting journey.

﻿

Hope to see you there!

We are now casting for our Halloween Party show .

The show will tour into community based venues, Nursing and Residential Homes, Day Centres.

We are seeking self-contained experienced hardworking singer/ performers who are keen to take quality musical shows to the community.

The Dates

Rehearsals –17th and 18th October in London

Playing Dates-20th -31st October-

We work Monday to Friday only.

The show is a one man/woman show so we are looking for experienced engaging performers with great singing voices,

We are looking for drivers with cars only

Please confirm where you are based in your application.

We offer £700 per week plus fuel on the road .

We are also casting our one man / woman musical show Winter Wonderland that will tour care homes and community based throughout December.

The show is production style show based on songs from the musicals Mary Poppins, White Christmas, Singing In The Rain, The Wizard Of Oz As well as traditional Christmas songs and carols, comedy routines and festive entertainment for all.

Playing dates 1st-23rd December

We are seeking self-contained experienced hardworking singer/ performers who are keen to take quality musical shows to the community.

The Dates

Rehearsals –17th and 18th October in London

Playing Dates-20th -31st October-

We work Monday to Friday only.

The show is a one man/woman show so we are looking for experienced engaging performers with great singing voices,

We are looking for drivers with cars only

Please confirm where you are based in your application.

We offer £700 per week plus fuel on the road .

We are also casting our one man / woman musical show Winter Wonderland that will tour care homes and community based throughout December.

The show is production style show based on songs from the musicals Mary Poppins, White Christmas, Singing In The Rain, The Wizard Of Oz As well as traditional Christmas songs and carols, comedy routines and festive entertainment for all.

Dates

Rehearsals 24th -28th November

Playing dates 1st-23rd December

We perform two 60 minute shows 6 days a week.

We are offering 600 .00 per week fuel on the road and accommodation allowance when required.

MUST BE A DRIVER WITH A CAR

Please email details including a singing reel to

info@theentertainmentproviders.co.uk

items.text:
🎬 Casting Call – Student Short Film

Synopsis:

In a world where emotional burdens are physical baggage, an old man struggles to carry his load through a park. He longs to climb a sunlit hill but is held back by his heavy suitcases. He repeatedly rejects the help of a mysterious, baggage-free blonde man who offers him a pair of scissors to cut the rope binding him to his past. After a failed attempt to build a shelter from his bags and a collapse that leaves him injured, the old man finally accepts the scissors. Realizing he has the power to choose his path, he cuts the rope, freeing himself from his burden. The blonde man vanishes, and the old man, now unencumbered, finally climbs the hill, symbolizing his newfound freedom.

KOLE JACKSON (DIRECTOR) KOLE.JACKSON.M -KOLE,JACKSON.M@GMAIL.COM @ GMAIL.COM AHAD KHAN ASSISTANT DIRECTOR) -AHADG8@ GMAIL.COM'

items.title: NAGRANIA SZUKAMY:

items.text:
Agencja Adliner Sp. z o.o. poszukuje lektorów - dzieci do animacji edukacyjnej 

Szczegóły: 
- nagranie w Warszawie prawdopodobnie pod koniec przyszłego tygodnia  
- lokalizacja nagrania - sadyba
- czas nagrania 2-3h 
- wynagrodzenie 500zł netto na Umowę o Dzieło (z przekazaniem praw bez ograniczeń czasowych na wszystkich polach eksploatacji) Jest to pierwsze z planowanej serii nagrań, więc jest możliwa kontynuacja współpracy 
- poszukujemy: 2 głosów chłopców i 3 głosów dziewczynek, w wieku 8 -13 lat 
- tematem nagrania jest ochrona środowiska, segregacja odpadów i recykling. W wyniku nagrania powstaną trzy krótkie animacje edukacyjne, które zostaną użyte w materiałach programu edukacyjnego kierowanego do szkół podstawowych.  

W celu zgłoszenia prosimy i wysłanie próbki głosu (nagranie telefonem) odczytującej poniższy tekst (odpowiednio dla chłopców i dla dziewczynek) na adres: [praca@adliner.pl](mailto:praca@adliner.pl) 
W tytule prosimy podać: "Głos chłopca/ dziewczynki do animacji edukacyjnej" a w zgłoszeniu prosimy o podanie danych kontaktowych rodzica (telefon komórkowy) 
Na zgłoszenia czekamy do 5 października 

Tekst dla Chłopców 
Dzieci są w fabryce papieru, Janek spogląda na duże bele z papierem i mówi: Wyglądają jak zwinięte latające dywany! Każdy papier ma taki kolor? Niebieski pojemnik jest początkiem drogi prowadzącej do prawdziwych skarbów!

Tekst dla dziewczynek
Dzieci są w zakładzie przetwarzania, przy maszynie separującej papier od plastik z opakowań wielomateriałowych.  
Ola mówi: Ale super! I nawet aż tak bardzo nie hałasuje. A nie lepiej od razu do właściwego pojemnika? Przecież to też jest kosz na odpady.

p.s. Proszę o niewysyłanie zgłoszeń w prywatnych wiadomościach

Anyone wanna check out CiveVita? We are proud to be partners with our neighbors on Campus here at Hollywood Park! 

I have tickets for the following dates. Send me a message if interested

Thursday, October 9
Friday, October 10
Sunday, October 12

Step into Tarantino Live: Pulp Rock Extravaganza—a cinematic rock concert reimagined inside one of the most breathtaking live venues in the world. Staged within CineVita, the largest Belgian Spiegeltent ever built, this immersive experience transforms a night out into a red-carpet-worthy escape. With 3,000 mirrors, hand-cut stained glass, and wood-carved detailing—all handcrafted by fourth-generation artisans—CineVita is more than a venue. Fueled by the unforgettable soundtracks of Quentin Tarantino’s films and brought to life by a world-class cast of singers, musicians, and immersive performers, Tarantino Live is a high-octane celebration of music, story, and style.

PIGE MED PROTESE SØGES TIL KORTFILM - (LØNNET) -ÅRHUS

Til kortfilmen “Dukkebarn” søger vi en pige med en ben protese eller arm protese til rollen som AURA. 

Lidt om filmen: 
“Dukkebarn udforsker den skrøbelige grænse mellem fantasi og virkelighed gennem øjnene på Aura. Hendes fascination til dukker bliver en måde at bearbejde hendes egen smertelige virkelighed og hendes forhold til sin krop. Gennem leg, skabelse og destruktion konfronteres hun med sine dybeste frugter og længsler. 

Alder: I mellem 6-12 år. 

Vi filmer i Århus d. 16-18 Januar 2026. Jobbet vil være lønnet, samt forplejning og transport. Søg gerne lige meget hvor i landet du bor. Vi ser gerne så mange som muligt;) 

Skriv til @Rirh.prod@gmail.com med emnet “CASTING -DUKKEBARN”. Skrive gerne lidt om dig selv, samt er billede og evt erfaring. 

Hvis du er gået videre til casting, eller fået rollen vil du få svar inden 10 Januar. 

Jeg glæder mig til at høre fra jer. 

Mvh Rebecca Renner Hansen - Dukkebarn film

Til kortfilmen “Dukkebarn” søger vi en pige med en ben protese eller arm protese til rollen som AURA. 

Lidt om filmen: 
“Dukkebarn udforsker den skrøbelige grænse mellem fantasi og virkelighed gennem øjnene på Aura. Hendes fascination til dukker bliver en måde at bearbejde hendes egen smertelige virkelighed og hendes forhold til sin krop. Gennem leg, skabelse og destruktion konfronteres hun med sine dybeste frugter og længsler. 

Alder: I mellem 6-12 år. 

Vi filmer i Århus d. 16-18 Januar 2026. Jobbet vil være lønnet, samt forplejning og transport. Søg gerne lige meget hvor i landet du bor. Vi ser gerne så mange som muligt;) 

Skriv til @Rirh.prod@gmail.com med emnet “CASTING -DUKKEBARN”. Skrive gerne lidt om dig selv, samt er billede og evt erfaring. 

Hvis du er gået videre til casting, eller fået rollen vil du få svar inden 10 Januar. 

Jeg glæder mig til at høre fra jer. 

Mvh Rebecca Renner Hansen - Dukkebarn film

items.text:
**CASTING CALL**

Til den ambitiøse og absurd-komiske kortfilm FLYT DIG, leder vi lige nu efter en række skuespillere. 

**LOGLINE**

En konfliktsky ung mand bliver udnyttet af sine venner og ignoreret af sin familie. Da hans rebelske fætter hjælper ham med at flytte, må han indse, at frihed ikke bare handler om at bryde ud – men om at turde definere sine egne grænser.

**ADAM **(hovedrolle, omkring 18)
* Ung af udseende
* Stille, meget almindelig, ikke særlig bemærkelsesværdig
* har svært ved at sætte grænser

**FAMILIEMEDLEM 1**

**FAMILIE MEDLEM 2**

**FAMILIEMEDLEM 3**

**FAMILIE MEDLEM 4**
* BIROLLER, ALLE mellem 40-80 år
* ALLE familiemedlemmer har replikker
* KØN/UDSEENDE er underordnet 

**ROOMIE 1**

**ROOMIE 2**

**ROOMIE 3**
* BIROLLER, DRENGE mellem 17-22
* ALLE roomies har replikker 
* UDSEENDE er underordnet

Optagelserne kommer til at ligge i Aarhus, omkring datoerne 14-15-16 oktober. Da dette er i samarbejde med Potemkin, Den Jyske Filmskole, er rollerne ulønnet.

Hvis man er interesseret i en/flere af rollerne, bedes man sende en mail på sara774g@gmail.som med alder og eventuel erfaring/showreel.

Vi glæder os til at høre fra jer!

Vh 

Sara Riahi, Freya Carlsen & Sylvester Byder

Details:
 • Location: Lagos, Nigeria
 • Return flights and accommodation will be provided
 • Must be available to start in early November
 • Must have a curvy figure and a fun, outgoing personality

If you’re interested, please send me a direct message including:
 1. Your current location
 2. Recent photos (to be shared with the client for selection)

It’s a great short-term opportunity to be part of an exciting venue and event season in Lagos!

🎭 FREE Introductory DRAMA Workshop For Young People In MANCHESTER This NOVEMBER 🎭

Join us at Red Players Academy for the FREE LAUNCH WORKSHOP of our BRAND NEW SATURDAY CLASS at our well-established and highly reputable drama school for young performers aged 9+

🌐 www.redplayersacademy.com/courses

🔴 RPA is Manchester’s elite-level drama school and talent agency – known for combining cutting-edge academic research with professional industry experience. Whether you’re just starting out or already experienced, our workshops are tailored to support every level!

🔴 We are an advanced training provider, offering advanced workshops in Acting, Drama, Movement, and Contemporary Performance. We teach all aspects of acting for both stage and screen, and are specialists in innovative and contemporary Creative Practice. 

🎬 Our students are currently appearing in:

📺 Netflix’s Adolescence
⚽ CBBC’s Jamie Johnson FC
🎭 13 Going on 30 @ Manchester Opera House
🔍 CBBC’s Odd Squad
…and more!

What you can expect at RPA:

🗓️Weekly Saturday classes in Altrincham
🎭 End-of-year showcase in a professional theatre
🎬 Acting for stage and screen
🎓 Taught by expert practitioners with 20+ years of experience
🌟 Curriculum is designed by acting coach & performance academic Lee Battle – credits include Coronation Street, Casualty, the BAFTA winning BBC drama The Street, Robin Hood, Awaydays and more
📣 Opportunity to join our SPOTLIGHT-registered Young Performers Talent Agency
🎬 Project-based, intensive, industry-focused learning environment

🗓️ LAUNCHING SATURDAY 1st NOVEMBER 2025

📍Limited spaces available – sign up to your FREE introductory workshop now!

📱 07441 396970
📧 info@redplayers.co.uk
🌐 www.redplayersacademy.com

sharedPost.text:
Casting Call

Production: Mother's Ruin, by Steve Bird (Back by popular demand!)

The story so far in the life of Liverpool comedian Garry Skyner, one of Britain's first- born victims of the Thalidomide medical disaster. Steve Birds play is a moving and emotional, yet hard hitting play about the highs, lows, struggles and sheer determination of a loving Mother and her son who refused to be beaten by the Government and company that profited from this medical disaster.

We are looking for a talented female actor playing range 20-30ys, who is from Liverpool or can do a convincing accent, for the lead role of Frances, Gary's Mum.
Frances is a spirited, humourous woman, who whilst having a heart of gold, has an inner strength, is tough, and fights for her child and what is right.
If you believe you are what we are looking for please send you CV and headshot to elainestewart46@yahoo.com 

Auditions to take place on Sunday 21st September 1pm-3pm at a Liverpool venue to be disclosed on receipt of CV, and a script will be provided. 

Performances will take place at the Epstein Theatre on 27th and 28th February 2026.

You must be available for rehearsals Sundays 1pm- 4pm (in Liverpool) starting 2nd November.
*This is a profit share production

KRAKÓW 

Halo Kraków :) Poszukujemy fajnych ludzi do naszego Teatru objazdowego dla dzieci.

Gramy w placówkach na terenie kilku województw - zazwyczaj wracamy do Krakowa każdego dnia i kończymy pracę w okolicach godziny 14/15, choć zdarzają się 3-4 dniowe wyjazdy.

Spektakle trwają 30 minut - ograniczona scenografia, bez dźwigania.

Średnio 3-4 spektakle dziennie (czasami 6-7).

Zawsze jeździ z nami organizator - nie wymagamy więc prawa jazdy .

Umowa zlecenie / dzieło.

Wynagrodzenie w zależności od doświadczenia.

Próby płatne.

Na wyjazdach zapewniamy wyżywienie.

Więcej szczegółów pod numerem 668 409 415

Można też do nas napisać na FB lub mailowo: biuro@teatrpompon.pl

Jeżeli lubicie pracę z dziećmi i macie z nimi fajny kontakt - zapraszamy :)

**POSZUKIWANI TANCERZE DO STUDENCKIEGO KRÓTKOMETRAŻOWEGO** **MUSICALU **🎬

Poszukujemy **pełnoletnich (18+) profesjonalnych tancerek i tancerzy** do filmu krótkometrażowego realizowanego w **Łodzi**.

🪩 Wymagania: umiejętność **partnerowania** oraz **dokładnego powtórzenia choreografii**. Tancerze i tancerki będą mieli również do wykonania **zadania aktorskie**.
🪩 Terminy zdjęć: **2-5.12 oraz 7–10.12 (5 dni zdjęciowych w tych terminach)**
🪩 Casting odbędzie się 5 października **w Warszawie** **o godz. 12:00**
🪩 Stawka wynosi 1000 zł za 5 dni zdjęciowych (bez prób).

📩 Zgłoszenia prosimy wysyłać na adres: **m.posiadalo@student.filmschool.lodz.pl**

W treści maila prosimy podać: **imię, nazwisko, krótki opis** oraz dołączyć **zdjęcie portretowe oraz sylwetki**.

**It's all about pure acting: playing the theme!**
***Secure your place and the early bird price until 15 October.***

3 x online workshops and 2 x individual coaching sessions with Christine Schmalor.

*“In my many years of practice, I have found that most actors have no problem portraying realistic characters, but are lost when it comes to abstraction. Yet this is exactly what contemporary dramaturgy demands. This means we have to develop a different acting consciousness with new techniques.”*

Welcome to the experiment of transforming your stage presence!

[https://online-theatre-academy.com/play-theme/](https://online-theatre-academy.com/play-theme/)

[https://www.facebook.com/events/2570098006696824](https://www.facebook.com/events/2570098006696824)

The Brookside Theatre, Romford is urgently looking for a male actor (playing age 45-60) for their Halloween production; THE ADDAMS FAMILY 

Role: Mal Beineke (Actor with good comic timing. Does need to sing a few lines but these are character vocals)
Accent: US (General or NYC)

Sadly due to an injury and subsequent surgery, the actor playing role has had to withdraw

Rehearsals: Weekday evenings and Sunday daytimes (some flexibility)

Show dates: 29th Oct - 2nd Nov 2025

Casper Black Casting is on the lookout for fun, engaging business owners based in or around London for a paid filming opportunity with Quickbooks.

🌟 **ΝΕΟΣ ΚΥΚΛΟΣ ΞΕΚΙΝΑΕΙ!** 🌟

Όλα στη ζωή είναι ρόλος…
Ποιος είναι όμως εκείνος ο ρόλος που θα σε συνδέσει με **τη χαρά, τη δημιουργία και την αισιοδοξία**;

🎭 Έλα μαζί μας και **ρίξε φως στα συναισθήματά σου** μέσα από τεχνικές που προσφέρουν **συνειδητότητα, αποφόρτιση και έμπνευση**, φέρνοντάς σε πιο κοντά στην καλύτερη εκδοχή του εαυτού σου!

Η μέθοδος απευθύνεται σε **όλους** όσους επιθυμούν να βιώσουν τη μαγεία των ρόλων και περιλαμβάνει:
✨ Διαχείριση έκφρασης & συναισθημάτων
✨ Υποκριτική
✨ Στοιχεία αυτοσχεδιασμού
✨ Γλώσσα σώματος
✨ Σωστή επικοινωνία
✨ Σκηνική παρουσία
✨ Ορθοφωνία
✨ Θεατρικό παιχνίδι
✨ Διαμόρφωση προσωπικής εικόνας
✨ Ηγετικές ικανότητες

💫 Εδώ και 20 χρόνια, η **Συναισθηματική Διαλεκτική** ρίχνει φως στα συναισθήματα και ανοίγει δρόμους αυτογνωσίας, χαράς και δημιουργίας.

items.text:
📣🎬 Casting Call – Short Mockumentary Film 

We are casting for ‘A Race with Ian Hitchworth’, a 3-minute mockumentary short film made as part of our final year at UWE Bristol. The film will be shot in Bristol in the week commencing 3rd November 2025 (exact dates TBC). This is a student project, unpaid, but with expenses covered. The film is intended for university showcase and festival submission.

Story:�Ian Hitchworth, son of a respected track runner, was once a rising sprint star. Years later, he resurfaces in a humiliating viral TikTok, and a small documentary crew captures his desperate bid to matter again—culminating in a shambolic charity race. Told in a deadpan, mockumentary style, the film mixes awkward comedy with moments of vulnerability as Ian’s arrogance clashes with his insecurities.

Roles:
Ian Hitchworth (Lead)�25, male. Wannabe track star with inflated self-belief and fragile confidence. To the camera, he’s arrogant, overconfident, and insists on being taken seriously — but cracks show through awkward silences and moments of panic. Actor must have strong comedic timing, improvisational instincts, and be comfortable with physical comedy (running, awkward costume, frustrated energy). Needs to balance deadpan humour with flashes of real vulnerability.

Interviewer (Supporting)�Any age/gender. Calm, inquisitive presence behind the camera, provoking Ian with offhand questions and blunt corrections. Think Nick Broomfield style: slightly awkward, matter-of-fact, not intentionally funny but often humorous through honesty. Delivery should be dry and understated. Voice-only, but may appear briefly on camera.

Race Official / Athletes (Supporting & Extras)�18–40, any gender. Includes a race official who ushers Ian onto the track (Small Speaking Role), plus authentic-looking athletes for the race sequence. Non-speaking, but must look natural on a track.

Apply by: 27th Ocotber 2025�To Apply: Please send a headshot, CV (or Spotlight/Mandy link), and any showreel/self-tape to Scarlet2.Gerry@live.uwe.ac.uk

Race Official / Athletes (Supporting & Extras)�18–40, any gender. Includes a race official who ushers Ian onto the track (Small Speaking Role), plus authentic-looking athletes for the race sequence. Non-speaking, but must look natural on a track.

Apply by: 27th Ocotber 2025�To Apply: Please send a headshot, CV (or Spotlight/Mandy link), and any showreel/self-tape to Scarlet2.Gerry@live.uwe.ac.uk

items.text:
ARE YOU AN ACTOR STUCK IN YOUR HEAD???

Yep... same. But I’ve been training with Steve Eastin and it’s honestly flipping everything upside down for me. You’ve seen this guy, he’s in like 200 movies [Catch Me If You Can, Con Air, Field of Dreams, Matchstick Men, etc.].

Not a lot of people even realize he’s teaching again. Feels like some random secret I lucked into.

What he does is just… different. Really different. Not about analyzing or breaking stuff down. It’s not gonna be for everyone but if you’re someone like me who gets trapped in overthinking, this is the kind of work that yanks you out of your head and dumps you right into the moment. If you live for those times where it feels like something else is taking over and you’re just along for the ride, this is that.

It’s rooted in Charles Conrad’s whole “choiceless awareness” thing. Basically stripping your brain of anything to hang onto and forcing you to just respond. No scene breakdowns, no making sure “beats” land. Just keeping it alive and messy and letting the work happen through you. If you’re curious, this article explains it better:

[[https://www.backstage.com/.../article/something-think-64356/](https://www.backstage.com/.../article/something-think-64356/)](https://www.backstage.com/magazine/article/something-think-64356/?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAYnJpZBExM2s0WGxFWTdncEhJTmxocgEeCVIM5HcT1y_cwi-yFme2XrGgrFIf-1zB9ic_Hs8B6I0eQe1Dy_6RVHYQfBM_aem_ZtitTlgW3beKBmQOc9GAQQ)

Class is super bare bones. Sit across, cold read, memorize, toss it, repeat. Just working the muscle of not thinking. Everything’s filmed so you’re used to being on camera too.

And the wild part, Conrad literally handpicked Steve to carry this forward. He taught for decades, everyone in casting knew his people, then he retired. And now he just randomly opened these tiny classes at his house. They’re small, intimate, and honestly feel like something that shouldn’t still exist.

If this even slightly calls to you, it’s a rare shot.

Classes here:

[[https://www.officialsteveeastin.com/](https://www.officialsteveeastin.com/)](https://www.officialsteveeastin.com/?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAYnJpZBExM2s0WGxFWTdncEhJTmxocgEeCVIM5HcT1y_cwi-yFme2XrGgrFIf-1zB9ic_Hs8B6I0eQe1Dy_6RVHYQfBM_aem_ZtitTlgW3beKBmQOc9GAQQ)

*FUNDET! 

Jeg søger en hundeejer med en sød familiehund (golden retriever, labrador, den slags, gerne i en lys farve) der kunne have lyst til at have deres hund med i nogle reklamebilleder/film der fremhæver sommerhushygge i Blokhus 😊🦮📷 

Vi laver nemlig nogle optagelser i Blokhus mandag-onsdag, hvor vi gerne vil have nogle scener med en hund. Det drejer sig om et par timer, gerne tirsdag eftermiddag, men andre tidspunkter er også mulige, og det er kun hunden der skal være med. Hunden skal agere sammen med en skuespilsfamilie. 
**Vi har 1500kr til betaling for dette.**

Skriv gerne en kommentar, send mig en besked eller mail på daniel@24copenhagen.dk, hvis du er interesseret.

God søndag!

CASTING CALL — FEMALE LEAD 🎬

Banbury, Oxfordshire | £250 for 2 days + travel considered

We’re casting for the final scenes of Failsafe, a psychological short film currently in production with a professional crew.

Directed by Rob Hutt — award-winning filmmaker of Time Spent (23 awards, 22 nominations, 8.8 IMDb rating). You can view Rob’s IMDb profile here:
👉 https://www.imdb.com/name/nm4254248/?ref_=ext_shr_lnk

This project is already generating festival momentum and will be featured in Pro Movie Maker Magazine.

ROLE:
 • Female, playing age 25–35
 • Character: A game designer whose reality begins to fracture, blurring with the world she created. Performance requires range: strength, vulnerability, psychological depth.

DETAILS:
 • £250 for 2 days filming.
 • Shoot will take place across one Saturday & Sunday, back-to-back.
 • Filming must be completed on one of the following weekends:
 • 11–12 October 2025
 • 18–19 October 2025
 • 25–26 October 2025
 • Location: Banbury, Oxfordshire. Reasonable travel costs considered.
 • Short film — to be submitted to national and international film festivals.
 • Professional set with full crew.
 • Self-tape auditions required.

📩 To apply / receive the self-tape brief:
https://www.starnow.com/casting/failsafe-3020838/female-games-designer-5368483/ or DM directly.

✨ This is a chance to be part of a powerful, festival-ready film with proven pedigree.

items.text:
**🎥 LØNNET JOB - CASTING CALL**

Vi søger en **herre i alderen 30-40** til et **videoshoot d. 10. oktober** i Storkøbenhavn.

**Tidspunkt:** 10. oktober - det præcise tidspunkt aftales nærmere, men optagelserne vil foregå tidligere på dagen.

Du vil blive instrueret hele vejen igennem. Der er **ingen speak eller replikker** - du skal blot gennemgå en typisk kunderejse, filmet i “flue på væggen”-stil.

Send mig en besked, hvis du er interesseret, så giver jeg flere detaljer.

items.text:
So proud to be the Executive Producer and Casting Director on Taro O'Halloran’s Short Horror Film  HUMANZEE starring Liz Bishop, Cheryl Pynn and introducing Zach Norton as Ziggy!! 

It is screening at Screamfest Horror Film Festival in Hollywood at Mann’s Chinese Theatre!

sharedPost.text:
Congratulations to Taro O'Halloran of Weymouth High School Class of 2020 on the screening of his Short Horror Film Humanzee starring Liz Bishop, Cheryl Pynn and introducing Zach Norton of Weymouth at Screamfest Horror Film Festival at the @TCL Chinese Theater in Hollywood!  

I am so honored to have the titles of Executive Producer and Casting Director on this film!

The hope is someone will see it and want to develop it into a Full Length Feature Film!

I see this film bringing home some awards!

My fingers are crossed for Taro’s Team!

Thank you Diane Purdy's Children's Theatre Workshop for giving me my own Stage from 9 to 49 and for letting me pass it on to John and Jake who brought Taro home from school one day and we all collaborated on multiple video productions with Diane’s costumes for years! 

https://2025screamfest.eventive.org/films/68d1b14f6ac811912ea77b5c?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTEAAR6Vy5trrNroF8v33cSuHpp_m2mf0qAtnnMljE9_T7BIh64lBOdHCOJWfuCTlQ_aem_eM-d05jAN52my1WjOr_zoQ

If you've got:
💫 A stunning, camera-ready look
🎩 Funky or formal fashion
🎬 A passion for being on screen
👠 Confidence, class, and style
Then this is your moment to step into the world of film, TV, commercials, and music videos — all PAID opportunities 💸
We’re looking for male and female talent who are ready to work and shine in front of the camera. Whether you're new or experienced, if you’ve got the look and professionalism, we want to hear from you!
📍 Cape Town -based only
📲 WhatsApp Moira McKie now: +27 68 499 9959
📸 To apply, send:
1 x l Headshot (no hats, no shades, no filters)

✨ All casting work is paid. We're only looking for serious, stylish, and beautiful individuals ready to break into the entertainment industry.
Join The Uzual Suspects Casting Agency – where your journey begins.

items.text:
***CASTING CALL FOR STUDENT FILM!!!***

***UNPAID & NON-UNION***

Location: Vancouver, BC

Film Dates: November 14th, 15th, & 16th with 2 rehearsals to be scheduled after casting

Casting "Confession", a student short film set in the late 1950s about a closeted devout Catholic who confesses his secret love for his priest during confession, only to discover the priest feels the same way.

Father Elias D'Arcy (white male, 25-35) - A devout Catholic priest who has been the head of Jacob’s church for a few years now, developing a close relationship with his parish. He came from a poor family, the child of Irish immigrants and the eldest of 6, he’s always had a nurturing nature to him and often helped others to the detriment of his own mental capacity. A closeted homosexual, Elias has delved deep into his religion and joined the priesthood to stave off any romantic connection, unwilling to come to terms with his sexuality.

Jacob McCarthy (white male, 25-35) - A devout Catholic and closeted gay man, his struggles with his raised religion and his sexuality being the catalyst for his story. He forced himself to marry a girl he was raised going to church with to promote a sense of normalcy and to please his family as the eldest child and only son expected to carry on the family name and reputation. He's unhappy with the life he chose to live for other people, feeling as though no one really knows him for who he truly is.

Actors will be compensated with a copy of the film, credit, and a meal every day of filming.

For audition scheduling and sides, please contact a.culp@infocusfilmschool.com

items.text:
CASTING CALL/ NON-UNION 

Casting Russian speaking roles in the short anti-war film 'During Winter, I Thought of My Father' written and directed by Danill Vasilyev. 

Please submit resume, headshot(s), and demo reel (if applicable) to duringwinter26@gmail.com to receive sides. 

Audition submission deadline: OCTOBER 18, 2025

Character descriptions below: 

ARTYOM

Russian speaking man, early 20s.

Description: Having seen the horrors of war firsthand, this young man became a conscientious objector who deserted the war. And despite paying a high price for his decision, losing a leg to frostbite, Artyom remains entrenched in his anti-war beliefs. A bright young

man from a middle-class family, who loves poetry and shoemaking, Artyom uses every ounce of his physical and mental might to get back to his family. 

VLADIMIR 

Russian speaking man, 50s-60s. 

A staunch patriot who was once a soldier too. A decorated one, whose pride in his heroic exploits for the Motherland could be felt from afar. But now, the old man stands alone. No family, no friends, no backing from the state which he holds so dear. His only son died

in a war years ago. All that’s left is the inextinguishable belief in his national identity, which has been built from years of tradition and pride. 

Rate: Unpaid, travel and food will be provided as well as top billing credits and IMDB credit.

Russian speaking man, 50s-60s. 

A staunch patriot who was once a soldier too. A decorated one, whose pride in his heroic exploits for the Motherland could be felt from afar. But now, the old man stands alone. No family, no friends, no backing from the state which he holds so dear. His only son died

in a war years ago. All that’s left is the inextinguishable belief in his national identity, which has been built from years of tradition and pride. 

Rate: Unpaid, travel and food will be provided as well as top billing credits and IMDB credit.

items.text:
🎬 Casting Call – Student Short Film

Production Title: Baggage

Director: Kole Jackson 

Role: Protagonist – Old Man

Requirement: Male actor in his 50s or 60s, preferably with a beard. Tall and skinny physique.

Shooting Dates: 18th – 19th September

As this is a passion-driven student short film, the role is unpaid, but catering will be provided throughout the shoot days.

Synopsis:

In a world where emotional burdens are physical baggage, an old man struggles to carry his load through a park. He longs to climb a sunlit hill but is held back by his heavy suitcases. He repeatedly rejects the help of a mysterious, baggage-free blonde man who offers him a pair of scissors to cut the rope binding him to his past. After a failed attempt to build a shelter from his bags and a collapse that leaves him injured, the old man finally accepts the scissors. Realizing he has the power to choose his path, he cuts the rope, freeing himself from his burden. The blonde man vanishes, and the old man, now unencumbered, finally climbs the hill, symbolizing his newfound freedom.

📧 If interested, please reach out to:

Kole Jackson (Director)– kole.jackson.m@gmail.com

Ahad Khan (Assistant Director)– ahadg8@gmail.com

items.text:
📣🎬 Casting Call – Short Mockumentary Film 

We are casting for ‘A Race with Ian Hitchworth’, a 3-minute mockumentary short film made as part of our final year at UWE Bristol. The film will be shot in Bristol in the week commencing 3rd November 2025 (exact dates TBC). This is a student project, unpaid, but with expenses covered. The film is intended for university showcase and festival submission.

Story:�Ian Hitchworth, son of a respected track runner, was once a rising sprint star. Years later, he resurfaces in a humiliating viral TikTok, and a small documentary crew captures his desperate bid to matter again—culminating in a shambolic charity race. Told in a deadpan, mockumentary style, the film mixes awkward comedy with moments of vulnerability as Ian’s arrogance clashes with his insecurities.

Roles:
Ian Hitchworth (Lead)�25, male. Wannabe track star with inflated self-belief and fragile confidence. To the camera, he’s arrogant, overconfident, and insists on being taken seriously — but cracks show through awkward silences and moments of panic. Actor must have strong comedic timing, improvisational instincts, and be comfortable with physical comedy (running, awkward costume, frustrated energy). Needs to balance deadpan humour with flashes of real vulnerability.

Interviewer (Supporting)�Any age/gender. Calm, inquisitive presence behind the camera, provoking Ian with offhand questions and blunt corrections. Think Nick Broomfield style: slightly awkward, matter-of-fact, not intentionally funny but often humorous through honesty. Delivery should be dry and understated. Voice-only, but may appear briefly on camera.

Race Official / Athletes (Supporting & Extras)�18–40, any gender. Includes a race official who ushers Ian onto the track (Small Speaking Role), plus authentic-looking athletes for the race sequence. Non-speaking, but must look natural on a track.

Apply by: 27th Ocotber 2025�To Apply: Please send a headshot, CV (or Spotlight/Mandy link), and any showreel/self-tape to Scarlet2.Gerry@live.uwe.ac.uk

Must look on track. dates Seeking contributors voluntarily travel expenses and food will be provided. Toapply send headshots &CV'sto'

items.text:
**Casting: Models für ein Haarstyling-Fotoshooting 📸**

Hast du Lust, vor der Kamera zu glänzen? Wir suchen Models mit allen Haartypen (lang, kurz, lockig, glatt, natürlich oder gefärbt) für ein kreatives und professionelles Fotoshooting in Berlin.

**Termin und Ort:**
📍 Berlin: **18. und 19. Oktober 2025**

**Projekt-Details:**
* Gage: **120 € pro Stunde**
* Alter: **18 – 35 Jahre**
* Teilnahme: ein oder beide Tage möglich
* Kostenübernahme: Reise- und Unterkunftskosten während des Shootings sind gedeckt

**Bewerbung:**
Bitte sende uns einige Fotos deiner Haare sowie eine kurze Vorstellung an: **manorycasting@gmail.com**

Eine tolle Gelegenheit, Erfahrungen auf einem professionellen Set zu sammeln und dabei Spaß vor der Kamera zu haben!

#CastingBerlin #HairShoot #ModelCasting #Berlin
